-- Taejoo Synthesis May Partner Freeport, Metorex, Katanga's Katumbi Says
-- B y   M i c h a e l   J .   K a v a n a g h
-- 2010-10-29T10:47:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-29/taejoo-synthesis-may-partner-freeport-metorex-katanga-s-katumbi-says.html
Taejoo Synthesis Steel Corp., a
South Korean company, has sent a delegation to the Democratic
Republic of Congo to discuss potential partnerships with mining
companies such as Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc. and
Metorex Ltd., Moise Katumbi, the governor of Katanga Province,
told reporters in Lubumbashi today.  The company will also look at mines and the 31-person
delegation met with Katumbi yesterday, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Michael J. Kavanagh in Kinshasa at 
 mkavanagh9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
